body: This PR fixes `float(obj)` when running with the limited api enabled.

comment_data.body: This looks like it's missing error checking. It should probably just be the same as the bytes version above (but with bytearray functions)
It seems worth testing that this code actually works and doesn't just compile by accident. You can add (Python) doctests that try different values.
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -73,7 +73,10 @@ def raises():
 
 def decode(bytes b, bytearray ba):
     return b.decode("utf-8") + ba.decode("utf-8")
-    
+
+def cast_float(object o):
+    return float(o)

comment_data.body: It's a srctree file so it's probably just easiest to add a few assets in run.py above rather than doctests
